===Etymology 1===
{{etymid|ja|ata}}
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|あた|alt=尺:uncommon}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|-}}.  First cited to the ''{{w|Kojiki}}'' of 712, with the phonetic spelling {{m|ojp|阿多|tr=ata}}.<ref name="KDJ2">{{R:Nihon Kokugo Daijiten 2|咫・尺}}</ref><ref name="K">{{R:Kojien}}</ref>

Possibly derived from verb {{m|ojp|当つ|tr=atu||to place one thing against another; to touch, to come into contact|pos=modern verb pair {{m|ja|当てる|tr=ateru|pos=transitive}}, {{m|ja|当たる|tr=ataru|pos=intransitive}}}}, from the sense of placing one's hand against something to measure it.

====Pronunciation====
{{ja-pron|あた}}

====Noun====
{{ja-noun|あた}}

# {{defdate|from 712}} {{lb|ja|historical|archaic}} {{n-g|roughly corresponds to the}} [[hand#English:_measurement|hand]] {{q|traditional unit of length; in Japan, described as originally the distance from the tip of the thumb to the tip of the middle finger (or possibly index finger) with the hand outstretched,<ref name="KDJ2"/><ref name="K"/><ref name="DDJS">{{R:Digital-Daijisen|咫}}</ref><ref name="DJR">{{R:Daijirin}}</ref> often defined as eight {{m|ja|寸|tr=sun||traditional inch}} or roughly 18cm<ref name="K"/>}}

